narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I think I have a dissertation topic now!

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Strengths: Critical engagement with academia as a whole, felt like I got to be a person and not a robot, got incredibly helpful feedback on my work, got to read everyone else's amazing work but in a way that made me feel excited rather than intimidated, formed new relationships with people who share my interests, gained pedagogical insights that helped me with my own teaching. Weakness: It is not the entirety of my grad school experience.

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: I would want to, because it was the best space I've been in while at Yale, but I probably wouldn't, because our community was so important to me that I feel very protective of it.
